External knowledge: 
- Admitted patients refer to those who have a recorded admission date; 
- Demographic data includes age and gender; 
- Most recent symptom severity implies the latest recorded symptom; 
- First treatment plan details refer to the earliest initiated treatment; 
- Latest test results refer to the most recently conducted tests; 
- The information is ordered by a unique patient identifier for organizational purposes.
